# Commit messages: one line only

When suggesting or writing a commit message (including Conventional Commits):

- Use **one line** — the subject line only.
- Do **not** add a blank line and body; no bullet lists or multi-paragraph explanations in the commit message.

If more context belongs elsewhere (PR description, `CHANGELOG`, ticket), put it there — not in the commit message.
